<item>
            <title>[PAY-4072] ach-returns: WFC AchInformation &#8594; MaxRedepositAttempts via accounts SB topic</title>
                <link>https://wellfit.atlassian.net/browse/PAY-4072</link>
                <project id="10016" key="PAY">Payments</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;New Wellfit.ServiceBus consumer in &lt;tt&gt;AchReturns.API&lt;/tt&gt; upserts &lt;tt&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;Returns&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;ReturnConfigurations&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt;.MaxRedepositAttempts&lt;/tt&gt; from &lt;tt&gt;WellfitConnect.AchInformation.Created&lt;/tt&gt;&apos;s &lt;tt&gt;ECheckRetryAttempts&lt;/tt&gt; field. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Single processor only (&lt;tt&gt;Worldpay_Card_Not_Present&lt;/tt&gt;, no fan-out); null/out-of-range values log + skip silently (no upsert, no DLQ); CHECK &lt;tt&gt;BETWEEN 0 AND 2&lt;/tt&gt; enforced in the handler, not bubbled to SQL; standard upsert (insert if absent, update if present). &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Includes a DDD refactor of &lt;tt&gt;ReturnConfiguration&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; private setters, parameterized ctor, &lt;tt&gt;UpdateMaxRedepositAttempts(int)&lt;/tt&gt; domain method with range guard, replacing the public-setter anemic shape. Handler pattern mirrors &lt;tt&gt;RedepositAttemptedMessageHandler&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;Routing (confirmed, no new infra):&lt;/b&gt; WFC&apos;s event already routes via the &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt; EG Domain topic &#8594; &lt;tt&gt;accounts&lt;/tt&gt; SB topic (staged in &lt;tt&gt;provision-sb-topics.sh&lt;/tt&gt; commit &lt;tt&gt;41f2da655&lt;/tt&gt;, &lt;tt&gt;&quot;accounts|submerchant-api|WellfitConnect.AchInformation.Created&quot;&lt;/tt&gt; &#8212; that line already serves PAY-4033&apos;s consumer). This item adds one more &lt;tt&gt;TOPOLOGY&lt;/tt&gt; line for &lt;tt&gt;ach-returns-api&lt;/tt&gt; on the same topic/event &#8212; no Terraform, no new topic.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Full analysis + solution: &lt;tt&gt;_bmad-output/products/payments/04_ExpresseLane/enhancement/wf-connect-ach-information-subscriber-ach-retry-config/&lt;/tt&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
